  "body": "# Feature Issue\n\nAdd a warning when users are trying to use the Wallet Send function directly to a smart contract. \n\nThis would important for preventing newbie users to make the common mistakes of sending tokens to a contract that does not accept it.\n\nRelated history:  https://twitter.com/NomiChef/status/1299960487153549312\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user without technical knowledge, I want to be warned when I am about to make a common mistake, such ash sending tokens directly to whatever I think is the right place.\n\n### Description\n\nWhenever a user tries to send any ERC20 token to an address where `eth.getCode(destinationAddress).lenght > 0` a warning is displayed like this (or equivalent message):\n```\n# Attention!\nYou are trying to send tokens to a smart contract, which can cause a problem because smart contracts cannot identify this interaction.\nSmart contracts consume tokens using a \"approve and call\" scheme, so it can identify your deposit and interact over it.\nIf you are trying to interact with a DApp, such as a DeFi project or crypto-game, then you are probably making a mistake, and you should use the \"Cancel\" button and inform yourself on how to properly interact with this DApp (it's probably using the Status Browser and navigating to the web3 enabled dapp page).\nIf you are trying to send tokens to another user, and therefore the destination address refers to a \"user controlled wallet\" (such as a Multisig, Gnosis Safe or similar) then you can check \"I know what I'm doing\" and dismiss this warning.\n\n[ ] Destination address is a user controlled address and I know what I'm doing. [ ] Don't ask me again for this address. [ ] Never warn me again.\n \n[Cancel this operation] [Continue to Send] \n```\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\nUsers are warned when sending ERC20 to a smart contract using the wallet send feature.\n\n### Notes\n\nThis does not apply to ETH, as for ETH smart contract can reject value sent.",
