    "body": "As @churik mentioned, the PR #11204 is only for \"pasting in the field of receipient\". \r\nI think is important to detect in any situation, for example, using qr code scanner to make this mistake is a possible scenario: \r\n1. a user coming from bitcoin (thinks that only transfer exists); \r\n2. reads about some protocol in his news feed; search more in the internet and ends up in the token smart contract of that project (usually the most visible smart contract);\r\n3. user scans the contract address qr-code in a block-explorer, to use it as destination to send tokens, in an attempt to participate in the protocol;\r\n4. rekt. ",
